features: Optimize cable management in limited spaces like ITX cases with the slim-type aluminum shell version, while ensuring effective internal ventilation. Please refer to the compatibility list before making a purchase.

Our angled adapters feature a strengthened PCB design that enables an angled connection without any wire bending. This ensures full contact with all cable terminals and eliminates the risk of thermal issues that can occur due to tight bending radii.

The perfect solution for users experiencing trouble with their RTX40' series graphics card power cables protruding too far from their PC case, preventing the side panel from closing properly; Please check the distance more than 16.3mm/0.64in between side plate and graphics card.
The terminals are crafted from high-quality alloy copper, for its exceptional conductivity and stability. This ensures a reliable and stable connection under high loading output in long term using.
600W high-current operation supported by an aluminum heat sink and ventilation holes, ensuring stable performance with optimal heat dissipation efficiency.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars 0 issues using this 180 degree adapter on my Zotac 4080 Amp Aero Extreme!
reviews.reviewText: I’ve had several EzDiyFab products and have nothing but good things to say about them. They have great quality control and their products never give me any issues. The fitment on this adapter is perfect, it does not wobble and it seats completely flat against the gpu 12vpwhr connector.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect Fit, Function, and Size
reviews.reviewText: This is a must have for anyone who is concerned about the bend radius of their 600W power cable attaching to a video card. Make sure your adapter is keyed properly to match your video cards, power connector. This is very important as it will not fit if it is not correct. Once again, make sure the connector and the power cable are seated properly. In my experience, it’s better to connect the power cable first, making sure the clasp catches on the power cable to the connector, and then plug the adapter into your video card that way you can’t accidentally push the adapter out of the video card while trying to the power cable. The adapter does get warm to very warm during full load again this is normal.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So far so good
reviews.reviewText: I'll admit i was somewhat skeptical with all the 12vhpwr mishaps in the past but I gave this a try as it fitted my needs perfectly for my case and color scheme. Works great so far. No measure of loss in power, laser measured heat at the connection and was also within acceptable parameters.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 18, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Easy to install and looks great. Much better than having the power cables on my RTX4090 being bent, especially with so many people having issues with the power cables catching fire. This item solves that problem. I tested it using benchmarking and it delivered the full 600watts the card can require. Highly recommend this adapter for anyone with the new 12 VHPWR cable for their graphics card.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 13, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Working great with my Asus 4090. Seems to run nice and cool even at maximum wattage as well as with overclocking.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Hasn’t melted yet
reviews.reviewText: Three stars because it doesn’t have a lock clip on the gpu side.
It fit my zotac card and tidied up the triple stock cable mess hanging over the rgb. I got a sleeved cable extension with it to drop over the top and down the back which really cleaned it up.

reviews.reviewTitle: SOLUCIÓN a tarjetas de video GIGANTES con gabinetes no tan ANCHOS
reviews.reviewText: Este adaptador es una JOYA si tu cable de la familia 4000 está muy pegada al panel de cristal, te explico todo...TAMAÑO:Todas las medidas de la publicación son correctas, puedes darte una muy buena idea con ver las medidas, sinceramente te evitas tener problemas de doblar por completo el cable 12VHPWR (completa basura por parte de nvidia), el adaptador tiene variantes, solo como consejo revisa la entrada de tu gráfica para pedir el correcto y apunte a donde necesites, puedes guiarte por la pestaña en la entrada de tu gpu.COMPATIBILIDAD:Es mis imagenes te dejo mi 4070 ti ROG STRIX OC, con la que es compatible 100%, lo unico que debes tener en cuenta con tu gráfica es el espacio de la entrada, hay algunos modelos que tienen un espacio muy grande (porque solo estaba considerando conectar un cable) por lo que es bueno que tomes medidas para que no vaya a chocar con las esquinas.GABINETES COMPATIBLESYo tengo un NZXT H9 Elite e incluso tengo un video en mi canal de youtube "El Macmado" en donde puedes ver la instalación de este adaptador y la guía para armar ese gabinete. Ese Gabinete es hermoso pero tiene un problema... casi todas las gpu's quedan pegadas al panel (además que las 4070 ti ROG STRIX es gigante), por lo que este adaptador es una verdadera JOYA.CALIDAD:No te voy a mentir, no se siente tan pesado como el de CABLEMOD, pero me sorprendió que a pesar de ser muy delgado tiene una firmeza impresionante al conectar tu cable, de hecho hasta cuesta un poco de trabajo desconectar tu cable, por lo que puedes estar tranquilo que no se desconectará facilmente.TEMPERATURAS:El adaptador es bastante seguro... En todo el tiempo que llevo usándolo (más de 6 meses) no he tenido ni un solo apagón, el primer día hice muchas pruebas con la cámara térmica de mi celular y apenas y se ponía tibio (con cyberpunk, apex, fortnite, diablo IV y todo en ultra), a pesar de tener un Lian Li Strimer V2 conectado al adaptador, se calentaba más el RGB de mi Lian Li Strimer V2 (por el rgb) que el mismo cable. Me sorprende que a pesar de ser delgado maneja muy buenas temperaturas y si esta versión disipa buen calor imagínate la que es un poquito más gruesa (esa vendría bien para las 4080, y 4090).SEGURIDAD Y ESTABILIDAD:A ver, hablando de seguridad hay MUCHAS variables a considerar, por que no va a faltar aquel que dice que quemó su gráfica por la irresponsabilidad e ignorancia de no saber utilizar componentes. Te dejo algunos consejos:- Primero revisa si tu fuente de poder es estable y de buena calidad (buena certificación).- CONECTA BIEN TODOS TUS CABLES (no dejes ninguno flojo, necesitas hacer presión para que entre bien LOL)- Puedes utilizar Daisy Chain (así lo tengo yo), el Daisy Chain está muy satanizado, pero porque la gente no sabe usarlo y es muy descuidada, aunque debes revisar si tu equipo se presta a ello,- Conecta al ultimo el adaptador para que no lo estés moviendo tanto.Aún así si tienes dudas puedes mandarme mensaje por cualquiera de mis redes "ElMacmado" y con gusto te respondo dudas.

reviews.reviewTitle: There were no reviews before purchase but I'm happy to report it's a solid product
reviews.reviewText: I needed an adapter to be able to close my computer case with my new 4080. I was originally going to purchase an adapter from Cablemods but they were sold out. These had zero reviews at the time of purchase so I took a gamble and bought it.Confirmed to fit using an Asus 4080 Tuf in a Lian Li O11 Dynamic case. The adapter itself has a nice metal finish and feels premium. It fits nice and snug on both the graphics card and cable.I ran a couple benchmark tests with and without the adapter and it made no difference in speed. Now if you're reading this review in the future and I haven't updated it, it means it's working fine. Otherwise if there is a problem I will update the review.Nice slim adapter for a decent price. Would definitely recommend it.P.S. make sure you order the correct connection type. The Asus 4080 Tuf requires the STD version.
